   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Eighty-three JESUS TASTED DEATH FOR MAN Scripture: Heb 2:9 The end man deserves The end man deserves is death.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Man s death sentence came from sin.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Since man lives in sin, his end shall be death.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Jesus tasted death for man Man s death has its source in his sin.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>When Jesus tasted death for man, He bore man s sin.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>That Jesus bore man s sin meant that He received the punishment for sin.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>That punishment was death.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Describe how Jesus tasted death for man, how He was forsaken by God, and how His heart melted like wax.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>He suffered the burning of the fire of God s wrath.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>These experiences are tastes of death.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The results of Jesus tasting death Man s sins were forgiven.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Man has been freed from the suffering of death.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Those who believe in Him do not perish and will be resurrected if they die.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>How to receive the effects of Jesus substitutional death</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Develop this point.</S>
